KCCAns:
Manure: During the preparation of field in most belly vegetables, manure 15-20 tonnes / hectare dung and 80 kilogram nitrogen, 50 kg phosphorus and 50 kg potash is needed.

Sowing: Make about 45 cm wide and 30-40 cm deep drains in the field. Keep the distance of one drain from one drain to 1.5 to 5 meters according to the cultivation of the crop. Put the water in the drains before sowing. When the quantity of moisture in the drain is suitable for sowing, then instead of sowing the soil in the form of sowing, it is 0.05 to 1.0 m Sow the seeds at a distance.

Time: Seasons of spring-summer harvesting in February-March and rainy season from July to July.

Irrigation: Irrigation from time to time as per the requirement of the crop, so that the crop health is good. Irrigation and sleeping-in drains.

Seed rate: Gourd 4-5 kg, Bitter gourd 6-7 kg, Pumpkin 3-4 kg, Turmeric 5-5 kg, Pepper Pumpkin 5-6 kg per hectare.

Yield: Gourd 250-420 quintals, bitter gourd 75-120 quintals, pumpkin 250-500 quintals, tomai 100-130 quintals, champcan pumpkin 50-60 quintals / hectare.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns:
The fertilizer is to be made from the waste, from which the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, the platform of 10x4 feet is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. 2 ridges are added to this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, fertilize 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sail for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top so that the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last In the stitches in 2 months, the number of earthworms inserted doubles, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure taken from the strains is dried and filtered in shade and stored in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Using Vermicum Wash, it would be good to have two exhaust drains on the platform so that the worm wash can be collected.

KCCAns: Fruits are born terminally on shoot growth emerging from mature wood.  To promote new shoots on all sides annual pruning is done after harvest is completed during December by shortening of past season shoot by removing one third of the shoot. Besides, dried, diseased and cross-cross branches and root suckers are removed. The tree is trained to get a single stem upto 60 cm with 3 or 4 scaffold branches. Thinning of flower clusters ensures better size of the fruit. Spraying liquid paraffin at 1 % concentration at 15 days interval twice during June reduces fruit cracking.

KCCAns:
1- Visit the field in which sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with hand and make a round pile by putting it on clean clothes. Remove the clay from finger to four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure until almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. Insert a notice sheet with a sample on which all the information is written, inside a plastic bag and outside a garment bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.

procedure :To prepare the compost from the waste is to make the pieces of glass and metal pieces separately, and after this, a 10x4 ft platform is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. Two ridges are added above this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, 3-4 quintals of dung manure and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which is irrigated by the Jhara for 10-15 days to reduce the temperature of the compost fertilizer. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation from the flame for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.
After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top. Thus, the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and in the last the earthworms survive, whose number In the stitches in 2 months, the number of earthworms inserted gets doubled, keep in mind that the manure is removed from hand.

Panchagavya- Panchagavya, an organic product has the potential to play the role of promoting growth and providing immunity in plant system. Panchagavya consists of nine products viz. cow dung, cow urine, milk, curd, jaggery, ghee, banana, Tender coconut and water. When suitably mixed and used, these have miraculous effects.
Cow dung - 7 kg, Cow ghee - 1 kg
Mix the above two ingredients thoroughly both in morning and evening hours and keep it for 3 days
Cow Urine - 10 liters, Water - 10 liters
After 3 days mix cow urine and water and keep it for 15 days with regular mixing both in morning and evening hours. After 15 days mix the following and panchagavya will be ready after 30 days.
Cow milk - 3 liters, Cow curd - 2 liters, Tender coconut water - 3 liters, Jaggery - 3 kg
